00:00:00.475 --> 00:00:02.273
Voiceover: Let's talk a
little bit about what it means

00:00:02.273 --> 00:00:06.068
to own shares or stock in a company,

00:00:06.068 --> 00:00:07.812
so shares or stock.

00:00:07.812 --> 00:00:09.405
I think we all have a general sense,

00:00:09.405 --> 00:00:10.352
but what I want to do in this video

00:00:10.352 --> 00:00:11.669
is make it a little bit more tangible

00:00:11.669 --> 00:00:14.102
to really understand
exactly what you're buying

00:00:14.102 --> 00:00:16.809
when you buy a share of stock.

00:00:16.809 --> 00:00:17.956
So the general sense,

00:00:17.956 --> 00:00:19.951
and this is exactly what it really is,

00:00:19.951 --> 00:00:22.136
is when you buy stock or you buy shares,

00:00:22.136 --> 00:00:23.952
you're essentially becoming a partial

00:00:23.952 --> 00:00:26.470
or a part owner of the company.

00:00:26.470 --> 00:00:31.254
Part owner of company.

00:00:31.254 --> 00:00:33.543
Just to contrast this with bonds

00:00:33.543 --> 00:00:35.597
because they're often kind of used

00:00:35.597 --> 00:00:36.874
in the same phrasing,

00:00:36.874 --> 00:00:38.697
"Oh, I'm gonna go buy
some stocks or bonds,"

00:00:38.697 --> 00:00:40.258
or "I deal with stocks and bonds."

00:00:40.258 --> 00:00:41.722
Bonds.

00:00:42.430 --> 00:00:46.877
Bonds, you become part
lender to the company.

00:00:46.877 --> 00:00:53.425
Part lender to the company.

00:00:53.425 --> 00:00:57.945
So, for example, if you buy a,

00:00:57.945 --> 00:01:00.743
well, I'll just say a face value bond

00:01:00.743 --> 00:01:03.214
of, let's say, it's $10.

00:01:03.214 --> 00:01:04.597
Let's say it's $1,000,

00:01:04.597 --> 00:01:06.546
and there's 1,000 people who do that.

00:01:06.546 --> 00:01:10.089
Each of you all are lending
$1,000 to the company

00:01:10.089 --> 00:01:11.803
and since there's 1,000 of you,

00:01:11.803 --> 00:01:14.009
you're lending $1 million to the company.

00:01:14.009 --> 00:01:15.348
I'm not going to go into detail in that

00:01:15.348 --> 00:01:17.844
because the focus of this
is going to be stock,

00:01:17.844 --> 00:01:19.014
but it's good to keep in mind

00:01:19.014 --> 00:01:20.490
that they're very different things.

00:01:20.490 --> 00:01:22.097
Here, you're owning the company.

00:01:22.097 --> 00:01:23.946
Here, you're lending to the company.

00:01:23.946 --> 00:01:26.099
So just to make this a
little bit more tangible

00:01:26.099 --> 00:01:27.803
of exactly what we're owning,

00:01:27.803 --> 00:01:29.348
