00:01:35.471 --> 00:01:41.764
Let's say we're dealing
with Company X right here,

00:01:41.764 --> 00:01:44.269
and let's say if we looked
at Company X's assets,

00:01:44.269 --> 00:01:45.404
and when we talk about assets,

00:01:45.404 --> 00:01:47.345
it really is the same thing that we mean

00:01:47.345 --> 00:01:48.919
in the real world, or in our everyday life

00:01:48.919 --> 00:01:50.144
when we talk about assets.

00:01:50.144 --> 00:01:51.650
The things that have value.

00:01:51.650 --> 00:01:53.255
Things that are going to give us

00:01:53.255 --> 00:01:54.838
some type of future benefit.

00:01:54.838 --> 00:01:56.392
A house is an asset because it gives us

00:01:56.392 --> 00:01:58.450
the future benefit of
being able to live in it

00:01:58.450 --> 00:02:01.184
and protecting us from
cold weather and rain.

00:02:01.184 --> 00:02:03.485
Cars are assets because they give,

00:02:03.485 --> 00:02:05.320
provide us some transportation.

00:02:05.320 --> 00:02:07.864
Cash is an asset because
it can be exchanged

00:02:07.864 --> 00:02:09.661
for things we need in the future.

00:02:09.661 --> 00:02:10.303
All of these ...

00:02:10.303 --> 00:02:12.896
A loan to someone else is an asset

00:02:12.896 --> 00:02:13.943
because in the future,

00:02:13.943 --> 00:02:15.319
they will pay us back.

00:02:15.319 --> 00:02:17.060
